IdentificationModule.BriefTitle: Multicenter Phase II Study of Apatinib in Patients With Advanced Breast Cancer(CABC006)
IdentificationModule.OfficialTitle: Multicenter Phase II Study of Apatinib in Patients With HER-2 Negative Advanced Breast Cancer With Chest Wall Metastasis

ResponsibleParty.ResponsiblePartyInvestigatorTitle: Head of the department of breast oncology

DescriptionModule.BriefSummary: The treatment of the patients with recurrent and metastatic breast cancer remains a major problem. There is still a lack of effective targeted therapy for Her-2 negative breast cancer.Based on the present researches on the anti-angiogenesis drugs in advanced breast cancer, the investigators believe that it is necessary to further explore the efficacy and safety of apatinib in advanced breast cancer.
DescriptionModule.DetailedDescription:
With the comprehensive treatment of breast cancer wildly used in the clinical practice, the life quality of the patients with breast cancer has been improved greatly, and the survival of the patients has been extended as well. However, the treatment of the patients with recurrent and metastatic breast cancer remains a major problem. There is still a lack of effective targeted therapy for Her-2 negative breast cancer.

Based on the present researches on the anti-angiogenesis drugs in advanced breast cancer, the investigators believe that it is necessary to further explore the efficacy and safety of apatinib in advanced breast cancer. The aim of this research is to evaluate the progression-free survival (PFS) of the patients with HER-2 negative advanced breast cancer with chest wall metastasis in the treatment of apatinib.

ArmGroup.ArmGroupDescription: Patients With HER-2 Negative Advanced Breast Cancer With Chest Wall Metastasis; Dosing regimen: apatinib tablets: 500 mg, Po, QD; 4 weeks as a cycle, continuous treatment until disease progression, death or intolerable toxicity (giving endocrine therapy simultaneously if hormone receptor positive)

Intervention.InterventionDescription: Dosing regimen: apatinib tablets: 500 mg, Po, QD; 4 weeks as a cycle, continuous treatment until disease progression, death or intolerable toxicity (giving endocrine therapy simultaneously if hormone receptor positive)

PrimaryOutcome.PrimaryOutcomeDescription: Progression is defined using Response Evaluation Criteria In Solid Tumors Criteria (RECIST v1.0), as a 20% increase in the sum of the longest diameter of target lesions, or a measurable increase in a non-target lesion, or the appearance of new lesions.
PrimaryOutcome.PrimaryOutcomeTimeFrame: evaluation per 2 cycles (8 weeks), up to 6 months;From date of randomization until the date of first documented progression or date of death from any cause, whichever came first, assessed up to 6 months

PrimaryOutcome.PrimaryOutcomeDescription: survival from first dose to death or last follow up
PrimaryOutcome.PrimaryOutcomeTimeFrame: evaluation per 2 cycles (8 weeks), up to 55 months

SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeDescription: Per Response Evaluation Criteria In Solid Tumors Criteria (RECIST v1.0) for target lesions and assessed by MRI: Complete Response (CR), Disappearance of all target lesions; Partial Response (PR), >=30% decrease in the sum of the longest diameter of target lesions; Objective response rate = CR + PR.
SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeTimeFrame: evaluation per 2 cycles (8 weeks), up to 55 months

SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeDescription:
Per Response Evaluation Criteria In Solid Tumors Criteria (RECIST v1.0) for target lesions and assessed by MRI: Complete Response (CR), Disappearance of all target lesions; Partial Response (PR), >=30% decrease in the sum of the longest diameter of target lesions; Progression Disease (PD), >=20% increase in the sum of the longest diameter of target lesions or appearance of new lesions; Stable Disease (SD), between PR and PD.

Disease control rate (DCR) = CR + PR + SD.
SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeTimeFrame: evaluation per 2 cycles (8 weeks), up to 55 months

SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeMeasure: Number of Participants With Adverse Events
SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeDescription: all kind of adverse events, including hypertension, proteinuria, nausea, fatigue, and bilirubin increase.
SecondaryOutcome.SecondaryOutcomeTimeFrame: evaluation per 2 cycles (8 weeks), up to 55 months
